---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="SOP Template Bundle" activePage="products" description="12 ICH E6(R2/R3)-aligned Standard Operating Procedures for clinical research sites. Editable Word + branded PDF, plus 11 companion forms. Ready to customize and implement." ogImage="/images/sop-previews/bundle-cover.png">

  <!-- Product Header — split layout, not centered hero -->
  <div class="product-top">
    <div class="product-hero">
      <div class="product-hero-text">
        <span class="product-badge">Digital Download</span>
        <h1>Clinical Research SOP Template Bundle</h1>
        <p class="product-tagline">
          12 Standard Operating Procedures covering the full clinical study lifecycle.
          Built on ICH E6(R2/R3), editable in Word, ready to brand for your site.
        </p>
        <div class="product-price-row">
          <span class="product-price">$249.99</span>
          <span class="product-price-note">or $29 per individual SOP</span>
        </div>
        <a href="https://buy.stripe.com/4gM7sLfLxa095iG0VT3gk02" class="buy-btn">Purchase Bundle</a>
        <p class="buy-note">Secure checkout via Stripe. Download link emailed instantly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="product-hero-preview">
        <img src="/images/sop-previews/bundle-cover.png" alt="SOP Bundle cover page showing all 12 included templates" />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Inline stats — horizontal, no border box -->
    <div class="product-stats">
      <div class="stat"><strong>12</strong> SOPs</div>
      <div class="stat-sep"></div>
      <div class="stat"><strong>11</strong> Companion Forms</div>
      <div class="stat-sep"></div>
      <div class="stat"><strong>95+</strong> Pages</div>
      <div class="stat-sep"></div>
      <div class="stat"><strong>PDF + DOCX</strong> Formats</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Preview Strip — horizontal scroll on mobile, flat on desktop -->
  <section class="preview-section" id="previews">
    <h2 class="preview-heading">Preview the Templates</h2>
    <p class="preview-sub">Cover pages and structure shown below. Full procedures, regulatory references, and responsibilities are inside each template.</p>

    <div class="preview-strip">
      <figure class="preview-fig">
        <div class="preview-img-frame">
          <img src="/images/sop-previews/sop-001-training.png" alt="SOP-001 Training and Qualification of Study Staff" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <strong>SOP-001</strong>
          Training & Qualification
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="preview-fig">
        <div class="preview-img-frame">
          <img src="/images/sop-previews/sop-007-data-management.png" alt="SOP-007 Data Management and Documentation" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <strong>SOP-007</strong>
          Data Management
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <figure class="preview-fig">
        <div class="preview-img-frame">
          <img src="/images/sop-previews/chk-012-close-out.png" alt="CHK-012 Study Close-Out Checklist" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <figcaption>
          <strong>CHK-012</strong>
          Close-Out Checklist
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Why Now — E6(R3) urgency + sponsor expectations -->
  <section class="why-now-section">
    <h2>Why Sites Need Updated SOPs Now</h2>
    <div class="why-now-grid">
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>ICH E6(R3) Is Here</h3>
        <p>The updated Good Clinical Practice guideline introduces Quality by Design, proportionate risk-based approaches, and expanded technology requirements. The EU GCP Regulation aligning with E6(R3) takes effect in 2026. Sites that haven't updated their SOPs risk non-compliance findings at their next inspection.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Sponsors Are Already Asking</h3>
        <p>Feasibility questionnaires now routinely ask whether your site's SOPs reflect E6(R3) guidance. Sponsors and CROs evaluate SOP currency during site selection. Outdated documents signal operational risk — and can cost you study awards.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Inspections Will Reference R3</h3>
        <p>FDA and EMA inspectors are incorporating E6(R3) expectations into their review frameworks. Data integrity (ALCOA+), risk-based quality management, and electronic record-keeping procedures are areas of increasing scrutiny. Your SOPs need to demonstrate these principles are embedded in your operations — not just referenced.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="why-now-card">
        <h3>Writing From Scratch Takes Weeks</h3>
        <p>A full SOP library is 12+ documents covering training, consent, data management, adverse events, IP handling, monitoring, and close-out. Writing each one from blank takes 20-40 hours of a qualified person's time. These templates give you a compliant starting point you can customize in days, not months.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What's Included — two-column: left = SOP list, right = sticky buy card -->
